WEBVTT

00:01.542 --> 00:02.793
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...

00:02.793 --> 00:04.175
YOU SET ME UP.
 I'M SORRY.

00:05.296 --> 00:07.258
I KNOW IT WAS YOU,
DANIEL.

00:07.258 --> 00:08.629
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

00:08.629 --> 00:09.890
WE CAN BUILD A FUTURE
TOGETHER.

00:09.890 --> 00:11.262
THIS IS MY FUTURE.

00:11.262 --> 00:13.134
YOU'RE ENDING THIS WITH ME.

00:13.134 --> 00:15.396
I THOUGHT I COULD AVENGE
MY FATHER'S DEATH BY MYSELF,

00:15.396 --> 00:17.098
BUT I CAN'T.
I NEED YOU TO HELP ME.

00:18.229 --> 00:20.441
CONRAD IS SUING VOULEZ
 FOR LIBEL.

00:20.441 --> 00:23.734
I'M WILLING TO DROP MY SUIT
JUST AS SOON AS YOU FIRE MY SON.

00:23.734 --> 00:25.526
IF YOU THINK WE'RE GONNA CAVE
TO YOUR THREATS, YOU HAVE --

00:25.526 --> 00:26.447
I'LL DO IT.

00:26.447 --> 00:27.648
JIMMY BRENNAN?
HEARD OF HIM?

00:27.648 --> 00:29.070
IF I'M TO BELIEVE WHAT'S
IN THIS POLICE REPORT,

00:29.070 --> 00:30.701
HE MAY ALSO GO BY
"DAD."

00:30.701 --> 00:32.363
WHAT DID JIMMY BRENNAN
DO TO YOU?

00:32.363 --> 00:34.205
HE KISSES ME,
AND I TRY TO PULL AWAY.

00:34.205 --> 00:36.117
AND HE PUSHES MY FACE
INTO THE CONCRETE.

00:37.158 --> 00:39.290
I WAS EXPECTING TO SEE
THE FORMER GOVERNOR'S WIFE.

00:39.290 --> 00:41.041
I'M THE FIRST MRS. GRAYSON.

00:41.041 --> 00:43.124
ARE YOU OKAY?
 SINCE MY HEAD INJURY,

00:43.124 --> 00:45.216
I'M GETTING A LITTLE DIZZY
SOMETIMES.

00:46.587 --> 00:50.221
YOU WERE MARVELOUS
LAST NIGHT, MRS. GRAYSON.

00:53.134 --> 00:56.307
Emily: OF ALL THE WEAPONS
 WE TAKE INTO BATTLE,

00:56.307 --> 00:58.599
THERE IS NONE MORE POWERFUL
 THAN THE MIND.

00:58.599 --> 01:02.143
IT HOLDS
 OUR INSTINCTS AND OUR TRAINING

01:02.143 --> 01:05.316
AND ALLOWS US TO DISTINGUISH
 FRIEND FROM FOE,

01:05.316 --> 01:07.108
LOVE FROM HATE.

01:07.108 --> 01:09.280
Dr. Sturman: HOLD
PERFECTLY STILL, MRS. GRAYSON.

01:09.280 --> 01:10.901
BUT IF THAT WEAPON IS UNSOUND,

01:10.901 --> 01:13.404
IT IS BY NO MEANS DISARMED.

01:13.404 --> 01:16.867
FOR THE MIND IS ALL THE MORE
 DANGEROUS WHEN DAMAGED.

01:16.867 --> 01:19.160
AND THERE'S NO GUARANTEE

01:19.160 --> 01:22.663
THAT IT WON'T CHOOSE ITSELF
 AS ITS NEXT VICTIM.

01:22.663 --> 01:24.084
Dr. Sturman: PHYSICALLY,

01:24.084 --> 01:26.837
YOU'VE RECOVERED
BEYOND EXPECTATION.

01:26.837 --> 01:28.969
WITH REGARD
TO YOUR HEAD TRAUMA,

01:28.969 --> 01:31.972
THERE ARE NO PERMANENT
NEUROLOGICAL PROBLEMS EVIDENT.

01:31.972 --> 01:33.804
HOWEVER, THERE IS
A BIT OF SWELLING

01:33.804 --> 01:35.886
BETWEEN THE FRONTAL
AND THE LEFT TEMPORAL LOBES.

01:35.886 --> 01:37.478
WOULD THAT EXPLAIN

01:37.478 --> 01:39.480
THE POUNDING IN MY EARS,
THE BLACKOUTS?

01:39.480 --> 01:41.562
I'M NOT A NEUROLOGIST,
EMILY.

01:41.562 --> 01:43.144
BUT THE LAB
FORWARDED THE RESULTS TO ONE.

01:43.144 --> 01:45.105
HE'LL HAVE A BETTER ANALYSIS
FOR YOU TOMORROW.

01:45.105 --> 01:47.067
AND UNTIL THEN,
WHAT DO I DO?

01:47.067 --> 01:48.399
I...

01:48.399 --> 01:50.531
I COULD BE A RISK TO MYSELF,
TO OTHERS.

01:50.531 --> 01:52.032
GIVEN YOUR STATE OF MIND,

01:52.032 --> 01:54.445
MAYBE TALKING WITH SOMEONE
WOULD HELP.

01:54.445 --> 01:57.288
AT THE LEAST, IT MAY HELP YOU
REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED.

01:57.288 --> 02:00.501
BECAUSE YOU STILL CAN'T
RECALL ANYTHING, RIGHT?

02:00.501 --> 02:03.204
Conrad: I'M GLAD TO SEE
I AM STILL WELCOME.

02:03.204 --> 02:05.206
I THOUGHT YOU'D HAVE
CHANGED THE LOCKS BY NOW.

02:05.206 --> 02:07.127
WELL, I HAVE MORE IMPORTANT
THINGS ON MY MIND

02:07.127 --> 02:09.250
THAN YOUR DEPARTURE,
CONRAD.

02:09.250 --> 02:12.253
AS HAVE I WHILE I'VE BEEN
STAYING AT THE SOUTHFORK.

02:12.253 --> 02:14.465
I CAN ONLY IMAGINE
WHAT YOU'VE BEEN UP TO.

02:14.465 --> 02:17.428
ASIDE FROM HAVING OUR
SON FIRED FOR YOUR
AMUSEMENT, I MEAN.

02:17.428 --> 02:19.430
ACTUALLY...

02:19.430 --> 02:22.223
I'VE COME TO CARE
ABOUT MY NEW VENTURE.

02:22.223 --> 02:25.266
AND, SO THAT I MAY
APPROACH IT WITH A CLEAR MIND,

02:25.266 --> 02:28.439
I WANTED TO POP BY
IN ANTICIPATION OF
CONVENING OUR ATTORNEYS

02:28.439 --> 02:30.070
TO CEMENT OUR DIVORCE
TOMORROW.

02:30.070 --> 02:32.112
OH, I ASSUME, AS ALWAYS,
MY HOUSE WILL BE

02:32.112 --> 02:34.154
THE FIRST THING
YOU'LL FIGHT ME OVER.

02:34.154 --> 02:37.238
WHY INFRINGE ON THE
BEAUTIFUL MEMORIES
OF OUR FIRST DIVORCE

02:37.238 --> 02:40.871
BY RETREADING THE SAME DUELS
DURING OUR SECOND ONE?

02:40.871 --> 02:43.083
MRS. GRAYSON,

02:43.083 --> 02:44.625
THERE'S BEEN A FIRE
AT THE GALLERY.

02:46.457 --> 02:48.749
Margaux: I STILL
DON'T THINK WE SHOULD
HAVE LET OURSELVES IN.

02:48.749 --> 02:50.170
AH, THE REALTOR WAS LATE.

02:50.170 --> 02:52.713
BESIDES, I NEEDED TO
CHECK FOR SECURITY ISSUES.

02:52.713 --> 02:55.796
USING BREAK-IN SKILLS
I WAS UNAWARE OF.

02:55.796 --> 02:58.098
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
 OH.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.473
OH, MY ACCOUNT MANAGER
JUST QUIT.

03:02.473 --> 03:05.266
THAT'S THE THIRD PERSON
TO LEAVE

03:05.266 --> 03:07.017
SINCE THEY HEARD OF
CONRAD'S MANEUVER.

03:07.017 --> 03:10.070
DO NOT SAY
"I TOLD YOU SO."

03:10.070 --> 03:12.072
I'M TAKING
THE WAIT-AND-SEE APPROACH.

03:12.072 --> 03:14.655
THAT'S WHAT I DID
WHEN CONRAD BOUGHT
INTO THE BAR LAST YEAR.

03:14.655 --> 03:17.238
THIS IS JUST TO HURT DANIEL.
NOT ME.

03:17.238 --> 03:18.989
ALL RIGHT, LOOK.

03:18.989 --> 03:21.081
NO MORE CONRAD TALK.
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:21.081 --> 03:23.203
I DON'T WANT TO BRING IN
BAD MOJO RIGHT OFF THE BAT,

03:23.203 --> 03:25.916
'CAUSE...
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

03:25.916 --> 03:28.669
...I THINK
THIS MIGHT BE THE PLACE.

03:28.669 --> 03:30.541
BUT YOU'VE ONLY SEEN
TWO HOUSES.

03:30.541 --> 03:32.593
I KNOW, BUT MY DAD SAID THAT
WHEN YOU'RE LOOKING,

03:32.593 --> 03:34.595
THE FIRST ONE YOU LIKE
IS THE ONE YOU SHOULD BUY.

03:34.595 --> 03:36.837
THOUGH...

03:36.837 --> 03:39.300
ARE YOU SURE
YOU'D WANT TO LIVE HERE?

03:39.300 --> 03:43.304
I KNOW IT'S NOWHERE NEAR
WHAT YOU'RE ACCUSTOMED TO.

03:43.304 --> 03:46.477
I CAME HERE
TO START A NEW LIFE

03:46.477 --> 03:50.651
AND TO LEAVE THE ONE
I'D GROWN ACCUSTOMED TO
IN FRANCE FAR BEHIND.

03:58.409 --> 04:00.451
[ SEA GULLS CRYING ]

04:02.032 --> 04:04.164
SINCE IT'S MY BIRTHDAY
TOMORROW

04:04.164 --> 04:06.166
AND YOU PROBABLY
FORGOT AGAIN,

04:06.166 --> 04:08.329
I DECIDED I'D JUST
TELL YOU WHAT TO GET ME.

04:10.501 --> 04:12.252
OKAY, GUILTY AS CHARGED.

04:12.252 --> 04:14.925
SO YOU NAME IT,
AND IT'S YOURS.

04:14.925 --> 04:18.928
I WAS REJECTED
FROM THE DESIGN INSTITUTE.

04:18.928 --> 04:22.222
I THOUGHT I HAD A SHOT,
BUT I GUESS THEY THOUGHT
I LACKED EXPERIENCE.

04:22.222 --> 04:26.096
SO I WAS HOPING YOU COULD
FIND SOMETHING FOR ME AT VOULEZ.

04:26.096 --> 04:28.268
YOU WANT MY JOB?

04:28.268 --> 04:30.441
[ CHUCKLES ]
'CAUSE IT'S AVAILABLE.

04:30.441 --> 04:33.694
SEEMS THERE'S NO END
TO DAD'S INSECURITY.

04:33.694 --> 04:37.277
HE GOT ME FIRED AND
TOOK MY STAKE IN THE MAGAZINE.

04:37.277 --> 04:39.239
I'M SO SORRY, DANIEL.

04:39.239 --> 04:40.781
AT LEAST
USE IT TO YOUR ADVANTAGE.

04:40.781 --> 04:44.204
I GUARANTEE HE'LL FLEX
HIS SAGGING MUSCLES TO HELP YOU.

04:44.204 --> 04:45.866
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:45.866 --> 04:48.208
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

04:48.208 --> 04:50.000
I'D RATHER SPEND MY TIME

04:50.000 --> 04:52.583
THROWING YOU
AN EPIC BIRTHDAY PARTY.

04:52.583 --> 04:56.086
YOU CAN'T PULL ALL THAT TOGETHER
IN ONE DAY.

04:56.086 --> 04:57.468
YOU DESERVE IT, SIS.

04:57.468 --> 04:59.089
AFTER ALL,

04:59.089 --> 05:02.182
SEEMS PRETTY CLEAR IT'S...

05:02.182 --> 05:03.924
ME AND YOU
AGAINST THE WORLD.

05:06.767 --> 05:09.099
[ BREATHING SHALLOWLY ]

05:14.435 --> 05:16.106
WHAT HAPPENED?

05:18.068 --> 05:20.861
I-I CAME HERE
LAST NIGHT TO WORK,

05:20.861 --> 05:23.824
TRY TO DEAL WITH
WHAT YOU TOLD ME, AND I, UH...

05:23.824 --> 05:26.447
WELL, I-I GOT SO UPSET
THAT I, UH...

05:28.789 --> 05:30.330
THIS IS MY FAULT.
I'M SORRY.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.583
NO. NO, NO, NO.
IT'S MY FAULT.

05:32.583 --> 05:34.715
YOU SHOULD GO,
THOUGH, ALL RIGHT?
LET ME DEAL WITH THIS.

05:34.715 --> 05:36.587
NO. WE'RE
IN THIS TOGETHER.

05:36.587 --> 05:38.218
WOW.

05:38.218 --> 05:40.170
SOMEBODY REALLY DID A NUMBER
ON THIS PLACE, HUH?

05:40.170 --> 05:41.922
[ SIGHS ]

05:41.922 --> 05:45.386
I'M JIMMY BRENNAN,
THE CONTRACTOR YOU CALLED.

05:45.386 --> 05:48.138
I DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU HEARD ABOUT ME.

05:48.138 --> 05:50.230
IT MUST'VE BEEN GOOD,
RIGHT?

06:04.825 --> 06:05.986
HEY.

06:07.327 --> 06:08.989
ARE THOSE AIDEN'S?

06:10.370 --> 06:11.912
WHERE'S HE GOING?

06:11.912 --> 06:13.664
WHEREVER HE TELLS MY JET
TO TAKE HIM.

06:13.664 --> 06:15.085
IS HE HERE?

06:15.085 --> 06:16.877
SINCE I KNEW
YOU WERE COMING OVER,

06:16.877 --> 06:18.128
I TOLD HIM TO SCRAM.

06:18.128 --> 06:20.461
I...DIDN'T WANT TO

06:20.461 --> 06:22.883
CONFUSE AN ALREADY
CONFUSING SITUATION.

06:25.215 --> 06:26.967
DID YOU WANT TO
SAY GOODBYE TO HIM?

06:26.967 --> 06:29.139
[ SIGHS ]

06:29.139 --> 06:32.062
NO. IT'S PROBABLY
BEST THIS WAY,

06:32.062 --> 06:34.475
ESPECIALLY SINCE I
DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M
DOING HALF THE TIME.

06:34.475 --> 06:39.069
WHICH BRINGS US TO
WHY YOU WANTED

06:39.069 --> 06:42.152
12 HOURS OF SOUTHFORK
SECURITY-CAM FOOTAGE.

06:43.734 --> 06:45.235
OKAY.
 [ KEYBOARD CLACKS ]

06:45.235 --> 06:47.828
Nolan:
HERE YOU ARE ON THE PHONE.

06:47.828 --> 06:49.830
ANY IDEA
WHO YOU WERE TALKING TO?

06:49.830 --> 06:51.081
Emily: [ SIGHS ] NO.

06:51.081 --> 06:53.874
WELL, I BET CONRAD DOES.

06:53.874 --> 06:54.915
[ KEYBOARD CLACKS ]

06:54.915 --> 06:57.708
PICKS UP IN THE HALLWAY.

06:57.708 --> 07:00.090
YOU GO IN.

07:00.090 --> 07:02.042
CONRAD LEAVES.

07:02.042 --> 07:03.964
[ KEYBOARD CLACKS ]

07:03.964 --> 07:06.216
AT LEAST
HE WAS A GENTLEMAN.

07:06.216 --> 07:08.388
HE DIDN'T COME BACK
TILL 7:00.

07:08.388 --> 07:10.010
WHEN I WOKE UP.

07:10.010 --> 07:12.262
WHAT IS GOING ON
WITH YOU, EMS?

07:12.262 --> 07:14.515
BLACKOUTS?

07:14.515 --> 07:16.356
COLLUDING WITH CONRAD?

07:16.356 --> 07:18.979
MY C.A.T. SCAN
SHOWED SWELLING.

07:18.979 --> 07:21.522
WHEN THAT GOES DOWN,
I'M SURE WHATEVER
THIS IS WILL STOP.

07:21.522 --> 07:22.983
YEAH, BUT IS THAT
WHAT THE DOCTOR TOLD YOU

07:22.983 --> 07:25.155
OR WHAT YOU WANTED TO HEAR?

07:25.155 --> 07:27.197
SHE'S SENDING MY RESULTS
TO A SPECIALIST.

07:27.197 --> 07:29.119
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
TALK TO A THERAPIST.

07:29.119 --> 07:31.071
YOU KNOW I CAN'T RISK
TELLING A STRANGER THE TRUTH.

07:31.071 --> 07:33.283
YEAH, BUT ISN'T THAT A RISK
YOU'RE ALREADY TAKING?

07:33.283 --> 07:35.916
I HAVE SURVIVED ON MY OWN
THIS LONG.

07:35.916 --> 07:37.748
TRUST ME.
I CAN HANDLE IT.

07:37.748 --> 07:39.880
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

07:43.003 --> 07:45.215
YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

07:45.215 --> 07:47.297
WHO DO YOU KNOW
IN LOS ANGELES?

07:47.297 --> 07:49.219
HELLO?

07:49.219 --> 07:51.471
EMILY? STEVIE GRAYSON.

07:51.471 --> 07:53.854
IT'S NICE
TO TALK TO YOU AGAIN.

07:53.854 --> 07:55.806
YEAH?

07:55.806 --> 07:58.228
I'M IN TOWN, AND I'M READY
TO PROCESS YOUR DIVORCE.

07:58.228 --> 08:00.060
[ SIGHS ]

08:04.154 --> 08:07.067
I BEGGED YOU
TO LEAVE WELL ENOUGH ALONE.

08:07.067 --> 08:09.279
YEAH, THAT WAS BEFORE
YOU TOLD ME WHAT HAPPENED --

08:09.279 --> 08:11.742
BEFORE YOU TOLD ME THAT
YOU WERE FORCED TO SACRIFICE ME,

08:11.742 --> 08:13.574
MOVE ACROSS THE OCEAN
TO STAY AWAY FROM THAT GUY.

08:13.574 --> 08:16.206
AND I SPENT MY LIFE
BUILDING A WORLD

08:16.206 --> 08:17.998
TO ESCAPE WHAT HE DID.

08:17.998 --> 08:20.040
AND NOW
HE IS IN OUR SPACE.

08:20.040 --> 08:22.753
I SHOULD NEVER HAVE TOLD YOU
WHAT HAPPENED.
 WHY?

08:22.753 --> 08:25.175
SO I WOULDN'T FIND OUT
WHAT A MONSTER HE WAS?

08:25.175 --> 08:27.888
OR THAT
I'M A CHILD OF RAPE?
 [ INHALES SHARPLY ]

08:27.888 --> 08:29.259
I'M GONNA KILL HIM.

08:29.259 --> 08:31.011
PATRICK.

08:31.011 --> 08:33.013
PLEASE...
DON'T DO ANYTHING.

08:33.013 --> 08:34.433
IF I LOST YOU
BECAUSE OF THAT MAN...

08:34.433 --> 08:36.436
YOU ARE THE ONE GOOD THING

08:36.436 --> 08:38.398
THAT CAME OUT OF
THE WORST TIME OF MY LIFE.

08:38.398 --> 08:40.811
IT'S WHY
I HOLD YOU SO DEAR.

08:40.811 --> 08:43.984
NOW, I WANT YOU TO
FIRE THAT MAN NOW.

08:46.446 --> 08:49.529
Jimmy: ALL RIGHT. OKAY.
ALL RIGHT. GOT IT.

08:49.529 --> 08:52.072
Daniel:
CHARLOTTE LOVES HIS MUSIC.

08:52.072 --> 08:54.114
YOU REALLY THINK
YOU CAN GET HIM?

08:54.114 --> 08:57.117
FOR DANIEL GRAYSON,
I'LL CLONE HIM IF I HAVE TO.

08:57.117 --> 08:58.869
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:58.869 --> 09:00.330
AH, THERE SHE IS.

09:00.330 --> 09:02.923
LARISSA,
THIS IS MY WIFE, EMILY.

09:02.923 --> 09:05.045
DANIEL'S TOLD ME
EVERYTHING YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH.

09:05.045 --> 09:07.878
YOU'RE LUCKY TO HAVE
SUCH A STRONG MAN BY YOUR SIDE.

09:07.878 --> 09:10.170
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

09:10.170 --> 09:11.762
OH, I MIGHT.

09:11.762 --> 09:14.014
HE'S PULLING OUT ALL THE STOPS
FOR THIS BIRTHDAY PARTY.

09:14.014 --> 09:15.385
FOR CHARLOTTE?

09:15.385 --> 09:16.887
THAT'S NICE OF YOU,
DANIEL.

09:16.887 --> 09:19.850
I DO ALL I CAN
FOR THE PEOPLE I LOVE.

09:19.850 --> 09:23.023
I'M GONNA GO CHECK OUT
WHERE THE BAND SHOULD SET UP.

09:23.023 --> 09:24.184
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

09:27.187 --> 09:29.990
I HEARD YOU, UH --
YOU DIDN'T COME HOME LAST NIGHT.

09:29.990 --> 09:32.863
I'M SURPRISED YOU CARE,

09:32.863 --> 09:35.786
ESPECIALLY
AFTER YOU MAN-HANDLED ME.

09:35.786 --> 09:38.578
SOMETHING
I KNOW YOU'LL REGRET.

09:38.578 --> 09:41.622
NO, THE ONLY THING I'LL REGRET
IS MY MARRIAGE TO YOU.

09:46.006 --> 09:48.839
Conrad: BECAUSE PUBLISHING
MY MEMOIRS IN SERIAL FORM

09:48.839 --> 09:51.972
WILL ONLY HELP
TO INCREASE OUR CIRCULATION.

09:51.972 --> 09:54.174
AND WITH MY PEDIGREE,
I CAN GUARANTEE

09:54.174 --> 09:57.347
THAT MR. LeMARCHAL WILL SEE US
AS SOMETHING FAR MORE

09:57.347 --> 10:00.480
THAN A CURIOSITY
WHICH LIES AN OCEAN AWAY.

10:00.480 --> 10:02.062
WOULDN'T YOU AGREE,
MARGAUX?

10:02.062 --> 10:05.646
I NEED TO SPEAK
TO CONRAD ALONE.

10:05.646 --> 10:06.897
NOW.

10:10.230 --> 10:13.443
YOU HAVE NO RIGHT HOLDING
A CREATIVE MEETING WITHOUT ME.

10:13.443 --> 10:17.037
OH, I CAN'T HELP IT
IF YOU'RE HOUSE HUNTING
WHILE I'M SETTLING IN.

10:17.037 --> 10:18.999
I RUN THINGS AROUND HERE.

10:18.999 --> 10:21.121
AND NOT MY FATHER,
AS YOU SEEM TO BE IMPLYING.

10:21.121 --> 10:23.003
YOU ARE ABSOLUTELY CORRECT.

10:23.003 --> 10:25.796
HE CONTROLS
AN INTERNATIONAL MEDIA EMPIRE.

10:25.796 --> 10:28.338
MM-HMM, WHICH IS WHY
YOU'RE WASTING YOUR TIME

10:28.338 --> 10:30.510
HOPING HE'LL
CARE ABOUT THIS MAGAZINE.

10:30.510 --> 10:33.013
OR MAYBE YOU JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW TO GET HIS ATTENTION.

10:36.967 --> 10:42.022
[ UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYS ]

10:42.022 --> 10:42.893
OH.

10:42.893 --> 10:44.224
EMILY?
 YES.

10:44.224 --> 10:46.186
STEVIE GRAYSON.
 NICE TO MEET YOU.

10:46.186 --> 10:49.439
I THOUGHT IT BEST THAT WE MEET
SOMEPLACE OUT OF THE WAY.

10:49.439 --> 10:51.692
LET'S TAKE A BOOTH.
 YEAH.

10:51.692 --> 10:54.324
I ALWAYS LIKE HIDING OUT
IN THIS STOWAWAY.

10:54.324 --> 10:55.736
I KNEW
WE'D GET ALONG GREAT.

10:55.736 --> 10:57.157
I USED TO COME HERE
YEARS AGO.

10:57.157 --> 10:59.619
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR COMING AGAIN.
 YOU KIDDING?

10:59.619 --> 11:02.202
I'VE HANDLED
OVER A THOUSAND DIVORCES.

11:02.202 --> 11:04.334
NOTHING COMPARES
TO A GRAYSON MAN.

11:04.334 --> 11:07.667
ONLY THEY COULD GET
ME TO CROSS THE COUNTRY
FOR A KINDRED SPIRIT.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.629
SO, DOWN TO BUSINESS.

11:09.629 --> 11:12.052
DO YOU WANT TO STICK WITH
THE TERMS YOU SUGGESTED

11:12.052 --> 11:13.553
ON THE PHONE LAST NIGHT?

11:13.553 --> 11:15.595
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
WELL, UM,

11:15.595 --> 11:17.798
NOW THAT YOU'VE HAD THE NIGHT
TO SLEEP ON IT, I, WELL --

11:17.798 --> 11:19.679
I THINK I'D RATHER
GET YOUR OPINION.

11:19.679 --> 11:21.852
OBVIOUSLY,

11:21.852 --> 11:24.184
DANIEL CHEATING
IN YOUR RESIDENCE

11:24.184 --> 11:27.808
IS GROUNDS FOR ANNULMENT --
SLAM DUNK.

11:27.808 --> 11:30.310
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

11:30.310 --> 11:32.652
YOU KNOW, I --
[ SIGHS ]

11:32.652 --> 11:35.075
I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN GO THROUGH WITH THIS.

11:35.075 --> 11:37.818
DANIEL AND I -- YES,
WE'VE BEEN HAVING A HARD TIME.

11:37.818 --> 11:40.240
BUT...
MAYBE I'M OVERREACTING.

11:40.240 --> 11:42.783
YOU KNOW, I THINK WE COULD --
WE COULD WORK IT OUT.

11:42.783 --> 11:44.664
REALLY?

11:44.664 --> 11:46.456
LAST NIGHT,
YOU WERE CONVINCED OTHERWISE.

11:46.456 --> 11:48.919
IN FACT, YOU WENT AS FAR
TO SAY THAT

11:48.919 --> 11:52.002
YOU WERE ALSO
IN LOVE WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

11:52.002 --> 11:53.754
NO. IT'S JUST DANIEL.

11:57.097 --> 11:59.139
OKAY.

11:59.139 --> 12:01.101
YOU CAN TELL ME
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

12:05.605 --> 12:09.109
THAT LOOK IN YOUR EYES...
IS A LOOK OF LOVE,

12:09.109 --> 12:11.271
AND NOT FOR
THE MAN YOU MARRIED.

12:13.403 --> 12:16.817
[ HEARTBEAT POUNDING ]
 [ SIGHS ]

12:16.817 --> 12:19.029
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

12:33.543 --> 12:36.176
I CAN'T LOSE YOU.

12:36.176 --> 12:39.379
NOT TO MY PLAN OR TO NIKO.

12:42.302 --> 12:43.553
NO, EMILY.

12:43.553 --> 12:45.015
EMILY.
YOU CAN'T DO THIS NOW.

12:52.312 --> 12:55.235
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?
LET GO!

12:55.235 --> 12:56.736
[ PANTING ]

12:56.736 --> 12:57.988
LOOK, I HAVE TO GO.

12:57.988 --> 13:00.070
IF YOU WANT TO HAVE
A SENSIBLE CONVERSATION...

13:00.070 --> 13:02.282
I'LL CALL YOU FROM LONDON,
BUT THIS ISN'T HAPPENING.

13:14.754 --> 13:16.336
HAVE YOU BEEN TOLD
WHERE WE'RE GOING?

13:16.336 --> 13:18.008
[ GRUNTS ]

13:29.059 --> 13:31.101
[ GRUNTS ]

13:36.026 --> 13:37.988
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING, NIKO?

13:37.988 --> 13:40.530
AVENGING MY FATHER,

13:40.530 --> 13:41.942
LIKE I SAID I WOULD.

13:41.942 --> 13:45.615
YOU DIDN'T THINK
I'D FIND THIS...

13:45.615 --> 13:48.578
UNDER YOUR BED?

13:48.578 --> 13:50.450
SPEECHLESS?

13:50.450 --> 13:53.213
THAT'S FUNNY, AIDEN.

13:53.213 --> 13:55.255
BECAUSE YOU KNEW
EXACTLY WHAT TO SAY

13:55.255 --> 13:57.958
WHEN YOU SHOWED UP
IN JAPAN.

13:59.589 --> 14:02.632
AND WHEN YOU TRIED TO
SEND ME TO RUSSIA

14:02.632 --> 14:04.885
TO KILL SOMEONE
FOR A CRIME YOU COMMITTED.

14:06.967 --> 14:08.268
I CAN'T BELIEVE I NURSED

14:08.268 --> 14:09.769
MY FATHER'S MURDERER
BACK TO HEALTH.

14:09.769 --> 14:11.681
I DIDN'T MURDER HIM.

14:12.933 --> 14:15.605
WE FOUGHT LIKE WARRIORS.
HE ATTACKED ME, AND I DEFENDED.

14:15.605 --> 14:17.027
A DEATH WAS INEVITABLE.

14:18.818 --> 14:21.691
I WANTED TO TELL YOU,
AND ONE DAY, I WOULD HAVE.

14:21.691 --> 14:23.743
BUT YOU HAD TO
HELP EMILY FIRST.

14:23.743 --> 14:25.325
THAT WAS THE CODE
YOUR FATHER TAUGHT US.

14:25.325 --> 14:27.617
WE GO WHERE WE'RE NEEDED.
 OH, I'M COUNTING ON IT.

14:27.617 --> 14:29.950
I LEFT HER A CLUE

14:29.950 --> 14:32.122
JUST TO SEE IF SHE WAS REALLY
AS GOOD AS HE CLAIMED.

14:32.122 --> 14:36.046
AND WHEN SHE SHOWS UP HERE
TO SAVE YOU...

14:36.046 --> 14:37.497
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

14:37.497 --> 14:39.879
I'M GONNA KILL HER.

14:39.879 --> 14:41.341
WHAT?

14:41.341 --> 14:43.343
YOU TOOK SOMEONE I LOVE...

14:43.343 --> 14:45.095
ON THIS SPOT.

14:45.095 --> 14:47.347
YOU CAN WATCH
WHILE I DO THE SAME.

14:52.892 --> 14:56.726
WE'LL TELL HIM $5,000 A MONTH
IN CHILD SUPPORT,

14:56.726 --> 14:58.939
ANOTHER $5,000 IN ALIMONY,
AND --

14:58.939 --> 15:00.440
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

15:00.440 --> 15:01.861
KNOW WHAT? UH...

15:01.861 --> 15:04.074
I AM BACK TOMORROW.
JUST SIT TIGHT.

15:10.700 --> 15:12.032
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:12.032 --> 15:14.874
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN
YOU WERE BEHIND THIS, CONRAD.

15:14.874 --> 15:18.588
SO I ASSUME EMILY'S
WHOLE DIVORCE STORY WAS A SHAM?

15:18.588 --> 15:20.210
OH, NO. NO.
QUITE THE CONTRARY.

15:20.210 --> 15:23.673
EMILY WOULD BE WISE
TO RID HERSELF OF MY SON.

15:23.673 --> 15:26.926
THAT SAID...
I AM GLAD YOU'VE COME,

15:26.926 --> 15:29.309
ESPECIALLY AS
WE'RE NEIGHBORS.
 [ CHUCKLES ]

15:29.309 --> 15:31.551
YOU'RE LIVING IN A HOTEL?

15:31.551 --> 15:33.893
YEAH, WHILE EMILY'S CHOSEN

15:33.893 --> 15:36.226
TO NOT FOLLOW THROUGH
WITH HER INEVITABLE DIVORCE,

15:36.226 --> 15:38.318
THAT HASN'T STOPPED ME
FROM PROCEEDING WITH MY OWN.

15:38.318 --> 15:40.020
HM.

15:40.020 --> 15:42.112
AND ARE YOU PLANNING ON
TREATING VICTORIA

15:42.112 --> 15:43.984
AS HORRIBLY AS YOU DID ME?

15:43.984 --> 15:46.826
ACTUALLY,
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

15:46.826 --> 15:50.450
YOU KNOW, I REGRET THE WAY
I HANDLED THINGS BACK THEN

15:50.450 --> 15:53.743
AND WOULD LIKE THIS CHANCE
TO MAKE MY SINCERE AMENDS.
 HMM.

15:56.706 --> 15:58.999
YOU KNOW,
I WANT YOU TO READ THIS.

15:58.999 --> 16:02.502
I BELIEVE IT MAKES AMPLE
RESTITUTION FOR MY MISDEEDS...

16:02.502 --> 16:05.005
WITH THE ADDED BENEFIT
OF GIVING VICTORIA

16:05.005 --> 16:06.716
HER OVERDUE COMEUPPANCE.

16:06.716 --> 16:08.928
HMM.

16:11.051 --> 16:12.932
[ CHUCKLES ] THERE WAS
A PERIOD IN MY LIFE

16:12.932 --> 16:16.146
WHEN I WOULD HAVE
WANTED NOTHING MORE.

16:16.146 --> 16:18.018
BUT THERE'S ONE PROBLEM.

16:21.731 --> 16:23.693
I'M HAPPY NOW.

16:23.693 --> 16:26.026
OH, WELL...

16:26.026 --> 16:28.448
WHY DON'T YOU
GIVE THAT TIME?

16:28.448 --> 16:29.989
THAT ALWAYS CHANGES.

16:33.823 --> 16:36.996
YEAH, MOST OF MY CREW'S
ON ANOTHER JOB.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.998
BUT I COULDN'T
PASS UP THE CHANCE

16:38.998 --> 16:41.621
TO SLAP GRAYSON
ON MY CLIENT LIST.

16:41.621 --> 16:43.623
YEAH.

16:43.623 --> 16:45.215
[ SIGHS ]

16:45.215 --> 16:47.797
HEY,
YOU GOT THE POWER CUT?

16:47.797 --> 16:50.930
UH...THERE YOU GO.
YOU'RE ALL SAFE.

16:55.135 --> 16:57.397
SO, YOU ACCIDENTALLY
LIT THE BLAZE, HUH?

16:57.397 --> 16:59.559
YEAH, THANKS
FOR REMINDING ME.

16:59.559 --> 17:02.021
YEAH,
DON'T BEAT YOURSELF UP.

17:02.021 --> 17:03.853
LIFE'S A BITCH
IF YOU LIVE WITH REGRET.

17:03.853 --> 17:05.734
YEAH, WELL, YOU SEEM LIKE
THE KIND OF GUY

17:05.734 --> 17:06.906
WHO CAN JUST
MOVE PAST STUFF.

17:06.906 --> 17:09.239
ARE YOU KIDDING?

17:09.239 --> 17:11.701
THERE'S A TON OF CRAP
I WISH I HAD DONE DIFFERENTLY.

17:11.701 --> 17:12.742
LIKE WHAT?

17:12.742 --> 17:14.364
WELL, BEING
A BETTER HUSBAND.

17:14.364 --> 17:16.955
BEING A BETTER FATHER
TO THE BOY I SEE

17:16.955 --> 17:18.538
TWO DAYS A MONTH.

17:18.538 --> 17:20.960
YOU, UH...
JUST GOT THE ONE?

17:20.960 --> 17:22.040
YEAH.

17:23.833 --> 17:26.876
WELL, NO, ACTUALLY.

17:26.876 --> 17:29.008
YOU WANT TO TALK REGRET --

17:29.008 --> 17:30.930
BACK IN THE DAY
WHEN I LIVED IN THE BRONX,

17:30.930 --> 17:33.843
I FOUND OUT
I HAD ANOTHER ONE.

17:33.843 --> 17:35.765
FOUND OUT, HUH?

17:35.765 --> 17:37.347
MUST HAVE BEEN
LIVING THE SINGLE LIFE.

17:37.347 --> 17:40.560
HARDLY.
I WANTED TO BE WITH HIS MOTHER.

17:40.560 --> 17:43.563
BUT SHE BASICALLY
HID THE PREGNANCY FROM ME.

17:43.563 --> 17:47.317
JUST ABOUT KILLED ME WHEN
I SAW HER PUSHING THAT
STROLLER DOWN LEXINGTON.

17:49.068 --> 17:51.491
REALLY?

17:51.491 --> 17:53.823
Jimmy:
I MEAN, HOW WOULD YOU FEEL
IF YOU SUDDENLY REALIZED

17:53.823 --> 17:55.115
THAT THERE'S THIS PART OF YOU
OUT THERE SOMEWHERE

17:55.115 --> 17:58.037
THAT YOU
NEVER GOT TO KNOW?

17:58.037 --> 17:59.909
IT'S A DAMN SHAME.

17:59.909 --> 18:01.911
YEAH. YEAH. I KNOW.

18:01.911 --> 18:03.753
I-IT IS.

18:03.753 --> 18:05.335
BUT YOU DIDN'T HIRE ME

18:05.335 --> 18:07.507
TO HEAR MY LIFE STORY.

18:07.507 --> 18:10.420
IT'S JUST MY LONG-WINDED WAY
OF TELLING YOU

18:10.420 --> 18:12.672
THAT I CAN GET THIS
ALL FIXED UP AND NO ONE'S
WORSE FOR THE WEAR.

18:12.672 --> 18:14.594
YEAH, NO.
I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

18:14.594 --> 18:17.677
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES IT'S BETTER
JUST TO MOVE PAST STUFF.

18:17.677 --> 18:19.309
AND IF I DO MY JOB RIGHT,

18:19.309 --> 18:21.601
YOU'LL FORGET
ANYTHING BAD EVER HAPPENED.

18:35.995 --> 18:38.788
STEVIE GRAYSON?
 [ SIGHS ]

18:38.788 --> 18:41.120
IF THAT'S
WHAT YOU STILL CALL YOURSELF.

18:41.120 --> 18:43.333
IT IS, VICTORIA.

18:43.333 --> 18:44.624
HOW ARE YOU?

18:44.624 --> 18:46.796
WELL, IT SEEMS
I'M CONDEMNED TO REVISIT

18:46.796 --> 18:48.838
THE HORRORS OF MY PAST,
IF YOU MUST KNOW.

18:48.838 --> 18:50.920
I'M SORRY
YOU SEE ME THAT WAY,

18:50.920 --> 18:53.633
ESPECIALLY SINCE
THE LAST TIME WE SPOKE,

18:53.633 --> 18:55.094
YOU WERE
ON MY HUSBAND'S ARM.

18:55.094 --> 18:58.057
[ CHUCKLES ] I'M SURPRISED
YOU REMEMBER THAT AT ALL,

18:58.057 --> 18:59.929
CONSIDERING
YOUR LEVEL OF INEBRIATION.

18:59.929 --> 19:01.221
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:01.221 --> 19:03.893
BUT BEFORE I'M SUBJECTED
TO SIMILAR VERBAL ASSAULT,

19:03.893 --> 19:05.815
PLEASE EXCUSE ME --
IT'S MY DAUGHTER'S BIRTHDAY.

19:05.815 --> 19:08.768
OH, THE ONE FATHERED
BY DAVID CLARKE, RIGHT?

19:09.899 --> 19:13.863
YOU CERTAINLY HAVE
MADE PATERNITY QUITE A HOBBY.

19:13.863 --> 19:15.945
WHY ARE YOU HERE, STEVIE?

19:15.945 --> 19:17.327
FOR PAYBACK?

19:17.327 --> 19:19.539
BECAUSE YOU STILL SEEM
AS OUT OF SORTS

19:19.539 --> 19:21.371
AS YOU WERE
ALL THOSE YEARS AGO.

19:21.371 --> 19:23.913
YOU WON, VICTORIA.

19:23.913 --> 19:25.335
ISN'T THAT ENOUGH?

19:25.335 --> 19:28.668
THOUGH I GUESS
YOU'RE STILL TRYING TO TAKE

19:28.668 --> 19:30.840
WHAT I ALREADY HAVE.

19:30.840 --> 19:33.503
HM.

19:44.514 --> 19:46.606
Nolan: EMILY.
 [ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

19:48.938 --> 19:50.019
EMS.

19:50.019 --> 19:51.521
HEY.

19:53.403 --> 19:55.905
IT HAPPENED AGAIN,
DIDN'T IT?

19:55.905 --> 19:58.408
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
 I GOT WORRIED
WHEN I DIDN'T HEAR FROM YOU.

19:58.408 --> 20:00.410
IT JUST
NEVER OCCURRED TO ME

20:00.410 --> 20:03.703
THAT YOU'D COME HOME,
I GUESS.

20:03.703 --> 20:06.876
THE QUESTION IS,
WHERE WERE YOU BEFORE THIS?

20:06.876 --> 20:09.128
I, UM...

20:11.040 --> 20:13.543
I REMEMBER
BEING AT THE STOWAWAY.

20:13.543 --> 20:16.596
WITH CONRAD'S FIRST WIFE?

20:16.596 --> 20:18.718
EMILY,
THAT WAS YESTERDAY.

20:18.718 --> 20:21.761
DO YOU EVEN REMEMBER
WHAT YOU TALKED ABOUT?

20:21.761 --> 20:24.053
UH...

20:24.053 --> 20:26.846
APPARENTLY
WHEN I CALLED HER,

20:26.846 --> 20:29.689
NOT ONLY
DID I ASK FOR A DIVORCE,

20:29.689 --> 20:31.441
BUT I ALMOST
TOLD HER ABOUT AIDEN.

20:31.441 --> 20:33.943
PHEW.

20:33.943 --> 20:37.407
SO, BLACKOUT EM
SPEAKS THE TRUTH?

20:37.407 --> 20:39.819
I'M AWARE OF THAT, NOLAN.

20:40.990 --> 20:43.202
AND ARE YOU AWARE THAT

20:43.202 --> 20:45.955
YOU ARE
LIVING WITH THE ENEMY

20:45.955 --> 20:49.829
IN A PLACE WHERE THE TRUTH
COULD COST YOU YOUR LIFE?

20:49.829 --> 20:51.791
[ SIGHS ]

20:51.791 --> 20:54.424
MAYBE YOUR MIND JUST WANTS TO
THROW IN THE TOWEL, EMS.

20:54.424 --> 20:58.137
[ HEARTBEAT POUNDING ]
 [ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

20:58.137 --> 20:59.379
EMS!

21:01.591 --> 21:06.265
Together: [ Distorted ]
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU ♪

21:06.265 --> 21:10.099
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU ♪

21:10.099 --> 21:14.984
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY,
DEAR CHARLOTTE ♪

21:14.984 --> 21:19.699
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU ♪

21:19.699 --> 21:21.991
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

21:28.167 --> 21:30.540
♪ MAKE NO MISTAKE,
THESE ARE ANIMAL URGES ♪

21:30.540 --> 21:33.713
♪ MAKE NO MISTAKE,
THESE ARE ANIMAL URGES ♪

21:33.713 --> 21:36.796
♪ MAKE NO MISTAKE,
MAKE NO MISTAKE ♪

21:36.796 --> 21:39.509
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

21:39.509 --> 21:42.722
[ SINGING INDISTINCTLY ]

21:42.722 --> 21:45.264
NOLAN, CALL ME
AS SOON AS YOU GET THIS.

21:53.232 --> 21:55.815
WELL, DANIEL
THREW A BEAUTIFUL PARTY.

21:55.815 --> 21:58.277
I CAN'T BELIEVE
CHARLOTTE'S 19.

21:58.277 --> 22:00.940
A BIRTHDAY
BRINGS TO MIND MANY THINGS.

22:00.940 --> 22:03.363
FOR A PARENT,
IT STIRS UP MEMORIES

22:03.363 --> 22:06.075
OF A DAY
BLESSED BY A MIRACLE.

22:06.075 --> 22:09.248
A JOYFUL GIFT
CHERISHED FOR YEARS TO COME.

22:09.248 --> 22:11.330
SADLY, IT'S AN EXPERIENCE
YOU'LL NEVER HAVE.

22:13.292 --> 22:14.954
WHICH MAKES ME WONDER --

22:14.954 --> 22:16.335
WHO WERE YOUR PARENTS?

22:16.335 --> 22:18.418
WHERE DID YOU COME FROM?

22:18.418 --> 22:20.800
AND WHY ARE YOU
STILL HERE?

22:25.304 --> 22:27.387
OH, I WOULD BE HONORED

22:27.387 --> 22:29.228
TO HELP YOU
FIND AN INTERNSHIP.

22:29.228 --> 22:32.181
THE MAGAZINE
NEEDS MORE CAN-DO SPIRITS.

22:32.181 --> 22:34.644
THANKS, DAD.
I'LL MAKE YOU PROUD.

22:34.644 --> 22:36.185
Emily: A JOB AT VOULEZ?

22:36.185 --> 22:37.567
WHAT A WONDERFUL IDEA,
CHARLOTTE.

22:37.567 --> 22:40.740
AND ONE I TOLD YOU,
LIKE, 30 MINUTES AGO,

22:40.740 --> 22:42.241
WHEN YOU GOT HERE.

22:42.241 --> 22:44.444
OF COURSE. SORRY.

22:44.444 --> 22:47.827
♪ MAKE NO MISTAKE,
THESE ARE ANIMAL URGES ♪

22:47.827 --> 22:50.289
AND AT THE RISK
OF REPEATING MYSELF,

22:50.289 --> 22:52.331
KUDOS TO YOU FOR TAKING

22:52.331 --> 22:54.123
MY RECOMMENDATION
TO CALL MY EX-WIFE.

22:54.123 --> 22:56.205
HAVE YOU SPOKEN TO HER?

22:56.205 --> 22:59.258
I'M JUST CURIOUS TO HEAR
HOW SHE REACTED TO YOUR PLAN.

22:59.258 --> 23:01.300
I REMAIN OPTIMISTIC.
 HM.

23:01.300 --> 23:05.094
YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT
IF AT ANY MOMENT

23:05.094 --> 23:07.767
YOU FEEL UNSAFE
AROUND MY SON AGAIN,

23:07.767 --> 23:09.849
I'VE TOLD THEM TO
KEEP THAT SUITE

23:09.849 --> 23:12.351
AT THE SOUTHFORK
ON RESERVE FOR YOU.

23:12.351 --> 23:15.394
I'M FINE.
BUT THANK YOU, CONRAD.

23:15.394 --> 23:16.395
ALL RIGHT.

23:18.067 --> 23:20.319
REALLY?

23:20.319 --> 23:22.111
OKAY, THAT'S GOOD TO KNOW.

23:22.111 --> 23:23.823
THANKS FOR THE INFO.

23:25.284 --> 23:27.196
PLEASE.

23:27.196 --> 23:28.698
HEAR ME OUT.

23:28.698 --> 23:30.870
WHY WOULD I WANT TO LISTEN
TO SOMEONE WHO FIRED ME?

23:30.870 --> 23:33.032
YOUR FATHER FORCED MY HAND.

23:33.032 --> 23:34.874
IF HE HAD MOVED FORWARD
WITH HIS LAWSUIT,

23:34.874 --> 23:36.375
THE MAGAZINE
WOULD HAVE FOLDED.

23:36.375 --> 23:38.297
I'M TRYING TO SAVE IT...

23:38.297 --> 23:40.460
FOR BOTH OF US.
 YEAH, WELL, BOTH OF US

23:40.460 --> 23:42.381
ARE NO LONGER THERE
TO FIGHT FOR IT, ARE WE?

23:42.381 --> 23:45.384
THAT'S WHY
I WANTED TO SEE YOU.

23:45.384 --> 23:47.677
WHAT DO YOU KNOW OF
CONRAD'S RELATIONSHIP

23:47.677 --> 23:50.099
TO MY FATHER?

23:50.099 --> 23:52.221
PROBABLY THE SAME AS YOU.

23:52.221 --> 23:54.013
A WHILE BACK, YOUR DAD

23:54.013 --> 23:55.645
HAD SOME INVESTMENTS
AT GRAYSON GLOBAL.

23:55.645 --> 23:57.897
BUT THEY HAVEN'T
BEEN IN TOUCH IN YEARS.

23:57.897 --> 24:01.230
THEN WHAT WOULD HE WANT
WITH PASCAL'S ATTENTION NOW?

24:01.230 --> 24:03.272
I DON'T KNOW.

24:03.272 --> 24:06.906
BUT HE'S CERTAINLY FORMING
A LOT OF NEW PARTNERSHIPS.

24:06.906 --> 24:10.159
ONE IN PARTICULAR
I PLAN TO GET TO THE BOTTOM OF.

24:10.159 --> 24:12.662
KEEP IN TOUCH.

24:30.049 --> 24:32.301
[ LAUGHS ]

24:32.301 --> 24:33.472
Jimmy: VERY NICE.

24:33.472 --> 24:35.184
I WANT TO BE, YEAH.
 YOU GONNA LIVE THERE?

24:35.184 --> 24:36.686
CHARLOTTE, YOUR FRIENDS

24:36.686 --> 24:38.397
WERE ASKING FOR YOU
ON THE VERANDA.

24:38.397 --> 24:40.359
OH. NICE MEETING YOU,
MR. BRENNAN.

24:40.359 --> 24:42.401
AND A HAPPY BIRTHDAY
TO YOU.

24:42.401 --> 24:45.274
YOU'RE THE SPITTING IMAGE
OF YOUR MOM.

24:45.274 --> 24:46.696
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:49.699 --> 24:51.410
I-I DIDN'T MEAN TO
CRASH YOUR PARTY.

24:51.410 --> 24:53.322
I JUST NEED YOUR
APPROVAL ON THESE PAINT
CHIPS YOUR SON SELECTED.

24:55.705 --> 24:58.077
OH, WELL, I'M AFRAID
THAT HE AND I

24:58.077 --> 25:00.379
ARE GOING TO HAVE TO
DISCUSS HIS CHOICES.

25:00.379 --> 25:02.291
NO PROBLEM.
IT CAN WAIT.

25:02.291 --> 25:03.883
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

25:03.883 --> 25:05.504
[ SIGHS ]

25:05.504 --> 25:08.798
I...COULDN'T HELP
BUT NOTICE

25:08.798 --> 25:12.261
YOU STARING AT ME JUST LIKE THAT
IN THE GALLERY.

25:12.261 --> 25:13.683
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

25:13.683 --> 25:14.934
Woman:
IT'S TIME TO OPEN PRESENTS!

25:14.934 --> 25:16.435
WELL, IT TOOK ME TILL NOW
TO PICK UP ON IT.

25:16.435 --> 25:17.767
COME ON, EVERYONE!

25:17.767 --> 25:20.139
I UNDERSTAND. I MEAN,
YOU'RE THE EX-GOVERNOR'S WIFE.

25:20.139 --> 25:22.441
YOU HAVE TO
KEEP UP APPEARANCES.

25:22.441 --> 25:25.194
I RESPECT THAT.

25:25.194 --> 25:27.356
YOU'RE MISTAKEN,
MR. BRENNAN.

25:29.198 --> 25:31.701
MAYBE I AM.

25:33.823 --> 25:36.415
BUT I DON'T THINK SO.

25:36.415 --> 25:38.117
EXCUSE ME.

25:40.329 --> 25:42.582
I HAVE GUESTS TO ATTEND TO.

25:44.373 --> 25:45.715
GO.

25:45.715 --> 25:48.047
MAKE YOUR LITTLE GIRL'S DREAMS
COME TRUE.

25:48.047 --> 25:49.258
GOOD NIGHT.

26:00.439 --> 26:01.891
PUT IT AWAY.
 Nolan:
 CALM DOWN. TALK TO ME.

26:01.891 --> 26:03.603
ALWAYS
 HIDING BEHIND TECHNOLOGY,

26:03.603 --> 26:05.234
AFRAID THAT EVERYONE
 WILL FIND OUT WHAT A
 FREAK YOU REALLY ARE.

26:05.234 --> 26:06.816
I SAID PUT IT AWAY!

26:06.816 --> 26:08.988
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

26:08.988 --> 26:12.491
AND THAT'S WHEN
YOU HULKED OUT ON MY CELL.

26:12.491 --> 26:14.323
I HOPE THAT'S
THE ONLY THING I BROKE.

26:14.323 --> 26:16.195
[ CHUCKLES ]
OTHER THAN MY EGO?

26:16.195 --> 26:18.037
LOOK, THANKFULLY,

26:18.037 --> 26:20.039
MY PHONE
BORE THE BRUNT OF YOUR WRATH

26:20.039 --> 26:22.331
BECAUSE YOU MADE IT
TERRIFYINGLY CLEAR

26:22.331 --> 26:24.203
THAT YOU DID NOT
WANT TO BE FOLLOWED

26:24.203 --> 26:26.626
WHEN I TRIED TO STOP
YOU FROM GOING BACK
INTO THE LION'S DEN.

26:26.626 --> 26:29.298
I'M SO SORRY, NOLAN.

26:29.298 --> 26:31.510
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I SAID THOSE THINGS TO YOU.

26:31.510 --> 26:33.302
I CAN HANDLE IT.

26:33.302 --> 26:36.595
WHAT I CAN'T HANDLE
IS YOU FLYING WITHOUT A NET.

26:36.595 --> 26:39.889
I MEAN, DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT CONRAD'S MASTER PLAN IS?

26:39.889 --> 26:41.350
NOT YET.

26:41.350 --> 26:43.562
OH, GOD,
I WISH I COULD JUST

26:43.562 --> 26:47.486
KEEP YOU LOCKED UP HERE
UNTIL THE FULL MOON PASSES.

26:47.486 --> 26:50.189
I DO
HAVE MY GUEST ROOM BACK.

26:50.189 --> 26:51.530
[ SIGHS ]

26:51.530 --> 26:55.324
AIDEN CERTAINLY
LEFT ENOUGH CRAP HERE.

26:55.324 --> 26:58.447
YOU THINK HE WOULD'VE
MASTERED THE ART OF
PACKING AT THIS POINT.

26:58.447 --> 27:02.081
THOUGH MY PILOT SAID
HE NEVER SHOWED UP, SO...

27:02.081 --> 27:04.083
I DON'T KNOW. YOU THINK
MAYBE HE'S COMING BACK FOR IT?

27:04.083 --> 27:05.705
WAS THIS IN HIS ROOM?

27:05.705 --> 27:07.667
YEAH. WHY?

27:07.667 --> 27:09.208
IT GOES WITH TAKEDA'S SWORD.

27:09.208 --> 27:12.211
I WAS THE ONLY ONE
WHO HAD THIS.

27:12.211 --> 27:15.094
YOU DO THINGS THAT AREN'T YOU
DURING THESE BLACKOUTS.

27:15.094 --> 27:16.886
WHAT IF YOU PLANTED IT
FOR NIKO TO FIND?

27:16.886 --> 27:19.348
AND IF SHE DID, SHE KNOWS THAT
AIDEN KILLED HER FATHER.

27:19.348 --> 27:21.100
[ SIGHS ]

27:21.100 --> 27:22.601
I GOT TO GO.

27:37.867 --> 27:40.119
AIDEN.

27:40.740 --> 27:42.081
AIDEN.

27:42.081 --> 27:43.703
OKAY.

27:43.703 --> 27:45.334
I'M GONNA
GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

27:45.334 --> 27:47.496
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

27:47.496 --> 27:49.919
I KNEW YOU'D COME.

27:54.884 --> 27:56.886
LET HIM GO, NIKO.

27:56.886 --> 27:58.297
NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

27:59.638 --> 28:02.261
HE'S GUILTY
OF TOO MANY THINGS.

28:02.261 --> 28:04.263
LIKE KILLING MY FATHER,

28:04.263 --> 28:05.935
LYING TO ME ABOUT IT,

28:05.935 --> 28:08.567
CHOOSING A FAILURE OVER ME.

28:08.567 --> 28:11.190
YOU'RE OUT OF YOUR LEAGUE.
 YOU'RE OUT OF PRACTICE,

28:11.190 --> 28:14.023
EVEN IF WE WERE BOTH TRAINED
BY THE SAME GREAT MAN.

28:14.023 --> 28:17.236
BUT ONLY ONE OF US
WAS HIS FAVORITE.

28:18.738 --> 28:20.279
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

28:39.008 --> 28:41.300
Aiden: EMILY, NO!

28:41.300 --> 28:43.142
SHE DOESN'T DESERVE TO DIE.

28:44.433 --> 28:47.186
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

28:47.186 --> 28:50.229
EMILY. NO.

28:59.779 --> 29:02.822
YOU HAVE EVERY RIGHT
TO WANT TO SEE ME DEAD,

29:02.822 --> 29:05.454
BUT KILLING ME OR
EMILY WON'T GIVE YOU
THE PEACE YOU'RE AFTER.

29:05.454 --> 29:07.326
I LOVED YOU...

29:07.326 --> 29:09.168
AND YOU BETRAYED ME

29:09.168 --> 29:10.329
AND MY FATHER.

29:10.329 --> 29:11.330
NO.

29:12.872 --> 29:15.174
YOUR FATHER
DIED BY HIS OWN CODE.

29:15.174 --> 29:16.715
DON'T LET THE SAME
HAPPEN TO YOU.

29:18.257 --> 29:20.840
PLEASE, NIKO.

29:20.840 --> 29:22.301
GO.

29:48.787 --> 29:51.040
[ SIGHS ] CAN I GET YOU
ANYTHING ELSE?

29:51.040 --> 29:52.541
ONCE UPON A TIME,

29:52.541 --> 29:55.294
YOU ALL
MADE THE BEST SIDECARS.

29:55.294 --> 29:57.466
WHICH MEANS
YOU KNEW MY FATHER.
 MM-HMM.

29:57.466 --> 29:59.378
WELL,
THOSE WERE HIS SPECIALTY.

29:59.378 --> 30:01.300
SO, I CAN'T PROMISE
THAT I'VE GOT HIS SKILLS,

30:01.300 --> 30:03.973
BUT I'M HAPPY TO TRY
FOR A LOYAL CUSTOMER.
 I'M FINE, THANKS.

30:03.973 --> 30:07.516
I JUST WANTED TO STOP
BY FOR OLD TIMES' SAKE
BEFORE LEAVING TOWN.

30:07.516 --> 30:10.429
OKAY.

30:10.429 --> 30:13.602
IS THAT YOUR BOY?

30:13.602 --> 30:15.734
YEAH. IT'S CARL.

30:15.734 --> 30:17.396
NAMED FOR MY DAD,
ACTUALLY.

30:17.396 --> 30:20.069
GREAT SMILE.

30:20.069 --> 30:21.360
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:21.360 --> 30:23.282
STEVIE GRAYSON.

30:25.404 --> 30:28.497
JACK...PORTER, OBVIOUSLY.

30:30.369 --> 30:32.751
SO YOU'RE
CONRAD'S FIRST WIFE, HUH?

30:32.751 --> 30:35.004
WE ALL MAKE MISTAKES,
RIGHT?

30:35.004 --> 30:36.585
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

30:36.585 --> 30:38.257
AT LEAST YOU WERE SMART ENOUGH
TO LEAVE HIM BEHIND.

30:38.257 --> 30:40.219
SPOKEN LIKE
SOMEONE WHO KNOWS HIM.

30:40.219 --> 30:42.381
I WISH I DIDN'T.
[CHUCKLES]

30:42.381 --> 30:45.554
HE'S JUST CAUSED
A LOT OF PROBLEMS FOR MY FAMILY.

30:45.554 --> 30:48.017
HOW SO?

30:48.017 --> 30:49.929
IT'S LONG STORY.

30:49.929 --> 30:51.430
I'LL SAVE IT
FOR NEXT TIME YOU'RE IN TOWN.

30:51.430 --> 30:53.102
HEY.

30:55.274 --> 30:57.526
LOOKS LIKE IT'S TIME
TO GET THE LITTLE MAN TO BED.

30:57.526 --> 30:59.979
ALL RIGHT. COME ON.

30:59.979 --> 31:02.321
Babysitter: BYE, CARL!
 THANKS SO MUCH.

31:02.321 --> 31:03.943
SURE.
NO PROBLEM.

31:03.943 --> 31:05.364
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU,
STEVIE.

31:05.364 --> 31:07.286
YOU, TOO, JACK.

31:13.122 --> 31:15.204
[ Speed-dialing ]

31:15.204 --> 31:17.126
RACHEL, IT'S ME.

31:17.126 --> 31:19.048
CANCEL MY FLIGHT BACK TO L.A.

31:19.048 --> 31:21.840
AND GET ME
CONRAD GRAYSON'S CELL NUMBER.

31:27.266 --> 31:29.098
YOU DELIBERATELY
DEFIED ME!

31:29.098 --> 31:30.849
CONTINUING TO
EMPLOY THAT MAN,

31:30.849 --> 31:32.601
AFTER I SPECIFICALLY
ASKED YOU TO FIRE HIM?!

31:32.601 --> 31:34.273
I KNOW WHAT YOU TOLD ME,
ALL RIGHT? I COULDN'T DO IT.

31:34.273 --> 31:36.685
YOU HAVE TO DO IT.
 NO, ACTUALLY,
I DON'T HAVE TO.

31:36.685 --> 31:38.817
AND AFTER
LISTENING TO HIM, UH --

31:38.817 --> 31:41.280
MAYBE HE'S NOT A MONSTER
ANYMORE, OKAY? HE'S GOT REGRETS.

31:41.280 --> 31:43.282
HE'S GOT THINGS IN
LIFE HE WISHES HE HAD
DONE DIFFERENTLY.

31:43.282 --> 31:45.524
WHY ARE YOU CHOOSING TO
HURT ME IN THIS WAY?

31:45.524 --> 31:48.197
I'M NOT, MOM. I'M --

31:48.197 --> 31:50.739
I'M CHOOSING TO
GET TO KNOW HIM A LITTLE BETTER.

31:50.739 --> 31:52.621
THERE IS
NOTHING LEFT TO KNOW.

31:52.621 --> 31:55.494
HE CAME TO MY HOME
THIS EVENING -- MY HOUSE.

31:55.494 --> 31:57.496
HE MADE ADVANCES TOWARD ME.

31:57.496 --> 31:59.838
AND I SAW IN HIM
THE SAME HEINOUS MAN

31:59.838 --> 32:01.420
WHO DREW ME IN
ALL THOSE YEARS AGO.

32:01.420 --> 32:04.343
IT IS ME WHO'S
SUFFERING, PATRICK.
NOT HIM, LIKE YOU WANTED.

32:04.343 --> 32:06.175
Jimmy: LIKE YOU WANTED?

32:06.175 --> 32:09.548
[ CHUCKLES ]
FORGOT MY TOOL BELT.

32:09.548 --> 32:12.051
LOOK, JIMMY, WE --
WE SHOULD TALK.

32:12.051 --> 32:14.433
IT'S A LITTLE TOO LATE
FOR THAT.

32:14.433 --> 32:17.266
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I DIDN'T FIGURE IT OUT SOONER.

32:19.358 --> 32:21.360
VICKY HARPER.

32:21.360 --> 32:23.402
BEEN A LONG TIME.

32:23.402 --> 32:26.025
AND YOU MUST BE
THE KID THAT SHE STOLE FROM ME.

32:26.025 --> 32:29.278
QUITE THE HAPPY
FAMILY REUNION, HUH?

32:29.278 --> 32:31.450
HEY, KID.

32:31.450 --> 32:34.623
DID YOUR DEAR MOM
EVER MENTION TO YOU HOW
SHE USED ME BACK THEN?

32:34.623 --> 32:37.036
HOW SHE
TOOK ADVANTAGE OF MY HELP

32:37.036 --> 32:38.537
TO GET WHAT SHE NEEDED
OUT OF LIFE.

32:38.537 --> 32:40.749
AND HOW DID SHE THANK ME?

32:40.749 --> 32:42.581
BY GIVING YOU AWAY.

32:42.581 --> 32:44.633
I WAS 15 YEARS OLD,

32:44.633 --> 32:46.345
AND I WAS LOOKING FOR
SOMEONE TO TRUST,

32:46.345 --> 32:48.347
AND YOU PREYED ON THAT.

32:48.347 --> 32:50.139
YOU RAPED ME.

32:50.139 --> 32:52.351
YOU KNOCKED ON MY DOOR
THAT NIGHT. WE HAD A
DRINK. WE HUNG OUT.

32:52.351 --> 32:54.053
YOU SAID YOU WERE
FEELING ADVENTUROUS --

32:54.053 --> 32:56.095
THAT YOU WANTED ME
DOWN IN THAT BASEMENT.

32:56.095 --> 32:58.057
[ Crying ]
OH, YOU BASTARD!

32:58.057 --> 32:59.898
DON'T YOU DARE
WALK AWAY FROM ME.
 NO! KEEP YOUR HANDS
OFF ME!

32:59.898 --> 33:00.979
GET YOUR HANDS OFF HER!

33:00.979 --> 33:02.361
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

33:05.984 --> 33:08.407
OH, MY GOD.

33:08.407 --> 33:09.278
OH, GOD.

33:12.491 --> 33:14.073
WE NEED TO
CALL AN AMBULANCE.

33:14.073 --> 33:15.914
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

33:17.246 --> 33:20.209
AND HE PUSHES MY FACE
INTO THE COLD CONCRETE,

33:20.209 --> 33:23.001
AND HE WHISPERS,
"RELAX, HONEY."

33:23.001 --> 33:24.293
RELAX, HONEY.

33:39.398 --> 33:40.769
[ Weakly ] HELP ME.

33:43.482 --> 33:45.274
RELAX, HONEY.

33:56.955 --> 33:59.208
I'M FINE, EMILY.
YOU CAN GO.

33:59.208 --> 34:01.290
AIDEN --
 I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT.

34:01.290 --> 34:06.875
I GUESS I SHOULD BE THANKING YOU
FOR SAVING MY LIFE...

34:06.875 --> 34:10.299
BUT I WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN
IN JEOPARDY IF YOU HADN'T
HAVE PLANTED THAT SWORD.

34:10.299 --> 34:12.841
DO YOU HATE ME THAT MUCH?
 OF COURSE I DON'T.

34:12.841 --> 34:14.303
THEN WHY DO IT?

34:15.884 --> 34:17.266
I DON'T KNOW.

34:19.016 --> 34:22.981
BUT WHAT I DID...

34:22.981 --> 34:25.484
[ SIGHS ]
...THAT WASN'T ME.

34:30.319 --> 34:32.451
I'VE BEEN BLACKING OUT.

34:32.451 --> 34:35.784
ARE YOU SERIOUSLY
GONNA BLAME THIS ON SOME
KIND OF MENTAL BREAK?

34:35.784 --> 34:37.074
YOU THINK
I WANTED YOU DEAD?!

34:39.578 --> 34:43.871
IT'S LIKE WHATEVER...
STATE I WAS IN,

34:43.871 --> 34:46.255
I COULD SEE OUR REALITY.

34:46.255 --> 34:48.967
I'M NEVER GONNA
GIVE UP MY PLAN.

34:51.049 --> 34:52.880
I CAN'T GIVE YOU A FAMILY,

34:52.880 --> 34:55.974
A NORMAL LIFE.

34:55.974 --> 34:59.057
SO...
[ SNIFFLES ]

34:59.057 --> 35:01.980
I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE
I WAS TRYING TO PUSH YOU AWAY.

35:01.980 --> 35:04.353
SO WHY SHOW UP YESTERDAY

35:04.353 --> 35:05.814
AND THROW YOURSELF AT ME,

35:05.814 --> 35:07.986
LOOKING FOR
SOME KIND OF RECONCILIATION?

35:10.989 --> 35:12.821
OR IS THAT
NEWS TO YOU, TOO?

35:16.905 --> 35:21.119
AND JUST SO YOU KNOW...

35:21.119 --> 35:23.872
I NEVER NEEDED
ANY OF THOSE THINGS.

35:23.872 --> 35:27.456
I JUST NEEDED YOU.

35:27.456 --> 35:30.459
BUT YOU NEVER
GAVE ME A CHOICE, EMILY.

35:32.211 --> 35:34.923
GET HELP...

35:34.923 --> 35:37.386
BEFORE YOU DO SOMETHING ELSE
YOU'LL REGRET.

35:43.392 --> 35:45.644
MY PARTY WAS A BLAST,
DANIEL.

35:45.644 --> 35:47.726
SADLY,
NO POTENTIAL BOYFRIENDS,

35:47.726 --> 35:49.938
BUT, STILL, THANK YOU.

35:49.938 --> 35:51.860
[ CHUCKLES ]
STAY SINGLE, CHARLOTTE.

35:51.860 --> 35:53.232
LIFE'S FAR EASIER THAT WAY.

35:53.232 --> 35:56.034
I THINK EMILY'S
OUT TO GET ME.

35:56.034 --> 35:58.447
A BELLHOP AT THE SOUTHFORK
TOLD ME

35:58.447 --> 36:00.779
THAT SHE AND DAD ARE
WORKING TOGETHER ON SOMETHING.

36:00.779 --> 36:04.122
WHY WOULD SHE TRUST HIM
WHEN HIS MISTRESS SHOT HER?

36:08.837 --> 36:11.920
I'M NOT SURE.

36:11.920 --> 36:14.052
BUT, UH...

36:14.052 --> 36:17.095
THEY GOT CLOSE
WHEN HE THOUGHT HE WAS DYING.

36:17.095 --> 36:20.469
AND -- AND YOU KNOW HE ALWAYS
WANTED ME TO MARRY EMILY.

36:22.221 --> 36:25.564
LISTEN, I NEED YOU TO
HELP ME WITH SOMETHING.

36:27.806 --> 36:29.067
WHAT DO YOU
WANT ME TO DO?

36:29.067 --> 36:32.731
VOULEZ IS DAD'S
NEW BASE OF OPERATIONS.

36:32.731 --> 36:34.903
OKAY? NOW THAT
YOU'RE WORKING THERE,

36:34.903 --> 36:37.316
FIND OUT ALL YOU CAN
ABOUT WHAT HE'S UP TO.

36:38.737 --> 36:43.031
ALL RIGHT? LIKE I SAID,
IT'S JUST YOU AND ME NOW.

36:49.458 --> 36:52.791
THE POLICE CALLED
WITH AN UPDATE.

36:52.791 --> 36:55.884
THE CORONER SAID THAT JIMMY DIED
FROM MASSIVE BLOOD LOSS

36:55.884 --> 36:58.046
FOLLOWING
A FALL FROM HIS LADDER.

36:58.046 --> 37:00.719
HE RULED IT AN ACCIDENT.

37:02.681 --> 37:05.844
RIGHT, IT'S...AN ACCIDENT.

37:07.726 --> 37:10.148
WE'RE NOT GUILTY
OF ANYTHING, PATRICK.

37:10.148 --> 37:13.352
WHAT YOU DID,
YOU DID TO PROTECT ME.

37:13.352 --> 37:14.983
YEAH.

37:14.983 --> 37:17.486
BUT STILL...

37:17.486 --> 37:21.280
STANDING THERE TONIGHT,
WATCHING MY FATHER DIE...

37:21.280 --> 37:22.951
WHAT IS WRONG WITH US?

37:22.951 --> 37:26.535
WE'RE VICTIMS
OF OUR WORLD.

37:26.535 --> 37:28.707
OF MEN
LIKE JIMMY BRENNAN.

37:28.707 --> 37:31.209
BUT THIS DARK CHAPTER
IN OUR LIVES IS FINALLY OVER,

37:31.209 --> 37:32.751
AND WE CAN MOVE ON.

37:34.713 --> 37:37.135
I DON'T KNOW IF I CAN.

37:48.977 --> 37:51.440
PLEASE SIGN IT
AS YOU AGREED.

37:51.440 --> 37:54.653
I'VE HAD A LONG NIGHT
AND WOULD LIKE SOME
SOLITUDE IN MY HOME.

37:54.653 --> 37:56.815
WELL, THERE MAY BE
A SLIGHT WRINKLE.

37:56.815 --> 37:58.857
WHAT GAME
ARE YOU PLAYING NOW?

37:58.857 --> 38:01.069
SORRY I'M LATE, CONRAD.

38:01.069 --> 38:03.241
HOW LOW
YOU MUST HAVE STOOPED

38:03.241 --> 38:05.033
TO PUT THIS ONE
ON YOUR LEGAL TEAM.

38:05.033 --> 38:06.865
OH, SHE'S NOT
JOINING MY LEGAL TEAM.

38:06.865 --> 38:09.908
SHE'S MERELY HERE TO IMPART
SOME PERTINENT INFORMATION.

38:09.908 --> 38:12.210
COPIES OF
THE GRAYSON MANOR PROPERTY DEED.

38:12.210 --> 38:15.794
IT TURNS OUT THAT
THE LAND WAS ACTUALLY
PURCHASED BY CONRAD

38:15.794 --> 38:18.046
BEFORE OUR DIVORCE
WAS FINAL.

38:18.046 --> 38:21.340
AND WHILE I MAY NOT HAVE
GOTTEN MUCH MONEY IN THE SPLIT,

38:21.340 --> 38:24.633
I DID GET ALL UNDEVELOPED
REAL-ESTATE HOLDINGS.

38:26.845 --> 38:30.929
THIS HOUSE BELONGS TO ME.

38:30.929 --> 38:33.392
AND I WILL FIGHT YOU
UNTIL MY LAST BREATH.

38:33.392 --> 38:36.855
LET'S HOPE THAT'S SOONER
RATHER THAN LATER.

38:36.855 --> 38:39.858
BUT UNTIL THEN,
I OWN THIS PLACE.

38:39.858 --> 38:41.700
AND WANT YOU OUT
BY THE END OF THE WEEK.

38:41.700 --> 38:43.572
HOMELESS...

38:43.572 --> 38:46.575
AT YOUR AGE, VICTORIA --
WHAT A PITY.

38:46.575 --> 38:47.946
AND YOU.

38:47.946 --> 38:49.327
YOU'RE AN IDIOT

38:49.327 --> 38:51.289
IF YOU THINK
THIS MAKES US PARTNERS.

38:51.289 --> 38:55.083
YOU WREAK HAVOC
IN THE LIVES OF OTHERS,

38:55.083 --> 38:57.506
AND THAT IS ABOUT TO
CATCH UP TO YOU.

38:59.758 --> 39:02.260
Nolan: DOCTOR'S STILL OUT
ON YOUR PSYCHOSIS?

39:02.260 --> 39:04.463
SHE CALLED.

39:05.964 --> 39:08.967
THE ANOMALY IN MY SCAN
ISN'T CAUSING THE BLACKOUTS.

39:14.142 --> 39:17.235
WELL...I'VE BEEN
WORRIED SICK ABOUT YOU.

39:17.235 --> 39:19.648
AND THEN, UH...

39:19.648 --> 39:23.572
SOMETHING OCCURRED TO ME
ABOUT YOUR PAST.

39:23.572 --> 39:25.864
SOMEONE, ACTUALLY.
 NOLAN...

39:25.864 --> 39:28.487
LOOK, YOU HAVE TO
FACE THE POSSIBILITY.

39:28.487 --> 39:31.369
[ SIGHS ] I KNOW.

39:33.291 --> 39:35.414
MY MOTHER.

39:35.414 --> 39:37.666
SHE WAS YOUR AGE WHEN

39:37.666 --> 39:39.798
SHE HAD HER FIRST BREAK,
WASN'T SHE?

39:39.798 --> 39:42.170
WHEN SHE
TRIED TO DROWN ME.

39:42.170 --> 39:44.803
[ INHALES DEEPLY, SIGHS ]

39:44.803 --> 39:48.176
IF NOTHING EVER WORKED
FOR HER...

39:48.176 --> 39:50.138
WHAT HOPE IS THERE
FOR ME?

39:50.138 --> 39:53.181
DON'T DO THAT TO YOURSELF.

39:53.181 --> 39:56.685
THERE ARE PEOPLE HERE
TO HELP.
 WHO I'M DRIVING AWAY.

39:56.685 --> 39:59.778
I LASHED OUT AT YOU.
I JEOPARDIZED AIDEN'S LIFE.

39:59.778 --> 40:01.520
I'M STARTING TO GO AFTER
THE WRONG PEOPLE, NOLAN.

40:01.520 --> 40:03.361
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

40:03.361 --> 40:06.024
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

40:07.906 --> 40:10.028
[ SIGHS ]

40:11.530 --> 40:13.872
OKAY.

40:13.872 --> 40:16.625
GREAT, THANKS.

40:16.625 --> 40:18.296
I JUST NEED
THE LOAN APPROVED,

40:18.296 --> 40:20.709
AND THEN I CAN MAKE THE OFFER
ON THE HOUSE.
 WHAT?

40:20.709 --> 40:22.541
THE GUY SAYS I SHOULD HAVE IT
IN A COUPLE DAYS.

40:22.541 --> 40:24.633
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:24.633 --> 40:26.805
OH, BUT THEN I WON'T BE HERE
TO CELEBRATE WITH YOU.

40:26.805 --> 40:28.547
I KNOW.

40:28.547 --> 40:30.639
I'LL BRING YOU SOMETHING
FOR THE HOUSE BACK FROM PARIS.

40:31.930 --> 40:33.552
YOU SURE
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING?

40:33.552 --> 40:36.605
I HAVE TO FORCE MY FATHER
TO SEE ME.

40:36.605 --> 40:39.397
THAT'S THE ONLY WAY
HE'LL HEAR ME ABOUT CONRAD.

40:39.397 --> 40:40.819
ALL RIGHT.

40:40.819 --> 40:42.731
I'LL CALL YOU WHEN I LAND.

40:42.731 --> 40:43.862
OKAY.

40:47.566 --> 40:49.568
BYE.
 BYE.

40:55.784 --> 40:57.956
YOU CAN'T GET ENOUGH
OF THE OLD PLACE, CAN YOU?

40:59.958 --> 41:02.791
I'D ACTUALLY LIKE TO HEAR

41:02.791 --> 41:04.713
THE STORIES YOU ALLUDED TO
LAST NIGHT.

41:04.713 --> 41:06.715
ABOUT CONRAD?

41:07.926 --> 41:10.388
UM...

41:10.388 --> 41:13.011
IT'S NOT REALLY
ANY OF YOUR BUSINESS.

41:14.933 --> 41:16.685
ACTUALLY, IT IS.

41:16.685 --> 41:19.397
WHY?

41:19.397 --> 41:22.150
BECAUSE, JACK...

41:25.904 --> 41:28.026
...I'M YOUR MOTHER.
